1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a visual passwords system that relies on recognizing the speaker using the visual speech signal alone. This involves processing video recordings of the user's face and extracting feature vectors, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.SD (Sound): Although the proposed system is primarily based on visual speech recognition, it may also involve processing audio signals to some extent. Therefore, the paper could potentially fall under the sub-category of sound (cs.SD). 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper aims to increase security by proposing a new authentication method based on visual passwords. This falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The proposed system involves processing video recordings of the user's face, which is a form of multimedia data. Therefore, the paper could potentially fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves processing speech signals to extract feature vectors, which could potentially fall under the domain of computation and language (cs.CL).
